cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper is about robotic learning and the proposed RoboNet database for sharing robotic experience. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses learning algorithms and generalization in robotic controllers. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is relevant as the experiments involve vision-based robotic manipulation and the use of video frames. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of high-capacity models and learning algorithms for robotic control. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also relevant as the paper discusses the complexity and diversity of the real world and the need for generalizable robotic controllers.
